==German==
===Etymology===
Old High German ''breit'', Old Saxon ''brēd''
===Adjective===
'''breit'''
# having great [[width]], ''eine breite [[Straße]]'' (a [[wide]] street)
# often fig. ''Die [[Universität]] bietet ein breites [[Spektrum]] von Fächern an.'' (The [[university]] offers a [[wide]] [[variety]] of subjects.)
# hum. to be [[drunk]], ''Du bist [[ziemlich]] breit.'' (You're pretty drunk.)
#[[broad]]ly

